@startuml
!include ../../style.puml

title MTTF vs. MTTR: The Availability Formula

' [step1 {"name":"Modern System Timeline"}]
rectangle "Normal Operation\nLong uptime window\nMTTF = 100 hrs" as uptime #LightGreen
' [/step1]

' [step2 {"name":"Availability Formula"}]
rectangle "Repair Window\nShort outage and recovery\nMTTR = 1 hr" as repair #Salmon
uptime -> repair

rectangle "Availability (A)" as availability #LightBlue
repair -> availability
note right of availability
  **A = MTTF / (MTTF + MTTR)**
  Example:
  MTTF = 100 hrs, MTTR = 1 hr
  A = 100 / 101 ≈ **99.0%**
end note
' [/step2]

' [step3 {"name":"The Dominant Strategy"}]
rectangle "Two Ways to 99.9%" as strategies #LightYellow
availability -> strategies
note right of strategies
  **Option A**: Double Reliability (MTTF = 200)
  **Option B**: Halve Recovery Time (MTTR = 0.5)
  In distributed systems, **Option B** is often cheaper
  and more scalable than **Option A**.
end note
' [/step3]

' [step4 {"name":"Availability Comparison"}]
rectangle "Core Insight\nDistributed systems improve availability\nmore often by reducing repair time\nthan by trying to prevent every failure." as insight #E6F3FF
strategies -> insight
' [/step4]

@enduml
